Preconditions:
- The input array `arr` must not be null.
- The length of the input array `arr` must be greater than or equal to 1.
- The value of `k` must be greater than or equal to 1.
- The value of `k` must be less than or equal to 100,000.
- The length of the input array `arr` must be less than or equal to 100,000.
- Each element in the input array `arr` must be an integer.
- Each element in the input array `arr` must be between -10,000 and 10,000.

Postconditions:
- The modified array `arr` will have a length equal to the length of the input array `arr` multiplied by `k`.
- The maximum sub-array sum in the modified array `arr` will be returned as an integer.
- The returned maximum sub-array sum will be less than or equal to 10^9 + 7.